     	When Trying To Script, The main concept of the whole script is actually the process of something translated to certain scripting language, and adapted to the languages' own process or function. That 'Something' Can be Anything For Example "Fall Damage" Or "Ragdoll". Or The Script Can Be Traced Back To Algorithm
		]]
	},
	['5'] = {
		Content = [[
		      We can use the example process from the last topic to be written in script, This should be the process, as the last topic has defined on the steps
			Here's what we know from step defining process(Algortihm),
			This is the expanded process. THIS IS NOT IN A SCRIPTING LANGUAGE(Next Page)>>>
		]]
	},
	['6'] = {
		Subtitle = "Pseudocode",
		Context = 'An Example Of Pseudocode',
		Content = [[
		--Start
		--You want to buy something
		>You need to check the price
		>You have to check your money
		--You have to compare the price and your money
			>>If Your money is more than the price then "You can buy it"
			>>If your money is lower than the price then "You can't buy it"
		>>>If you can buy it then "buy it"
		--End
		]]
	},
	['7'] = {
		Subtitle = 'Symbol Breakdown',
		Context = 'Clarification of symbols on the previous page',
		Content = [[
		    In THE mess On The Last Page, Here is the meaning between each symbol
			">" Defines a variable
			">>" Defines The First Check In The Process
			">>>" Defines the Second Check In The Process
			Anyways, I'll not teach you about Checking Numbers if one is more or less, it's self-explanatory( =<, =>, <, >, ==, ~=[!=]) 
