			"
			It'll be
			"
			if Variable1 <= Variable2 then --> We have enough
			--Buy Function --
			else--We don't have 
			--Blank or smth--
			end
		]]
	},
	['13'] = {
		Content = [[
		      We don't actually have to write 'else' because nothing happened if we lack money. While 'end' is actually required
			You may notice 'Where is the second check'. There are ways to avoid it. The Second Check If Only Exist If you use another variable to define Buy ability and does another check outside these IfElse Statement. The most effective way is to just put the Buy Function there at the "--"(commented out) section.
		]]
	},
	['14'] = {
		Subtitle = 'Conclusion 1/2',
		Context = 'The whole book in a nutshell and final thoughts..',
		Content = [[
				After all that, I could potentially just say, Scripting ever is just a way to represent step to step movement or function that derived from logical consideration of process(Algorithm),
